    "_postman_id": "3a968279-3c62-47c1-ac7a-90bdf9abfeb2",
    "name": "Snow Rush",
    "description": "# Snow Rush API\n\nSnow Rush is an e-commerce REST API built for a ski and snowboard shop. It provides a complete backend for managing products, user authentication, shopping baskets, and order processing — everything needed to power a modern winter sports retail experience.\n\n---\n\n## Feature Areas\n\n### Authentication\nHandles user registration, login (for both regular users and admins), retrieving authenticated user info, and logout. All protected endpoints require a valid token obtained after login.\n\n### Products\nFull product management including listing all products, retrieving a single product, creating and editing products with file uploads, and deleting products. Admin privileges are required for write operations.\n\n### Filtering\nAdvanced product discovery through sorting, searching, filtering by brand and/or type, combining multiple filters, and pagination. Use these endpoints to build rich product browsing experiences.\n\n### Basket\nManage the shopping basket — retrieve the current basket, add items, and remove items. The basket is tied to the authenticated user's session.\n\n### Orders & Payments\nCreate payment intents, place orders, retrieve a list of orders, and get detailed information about a specific order. Integrates with a payment provider to handle checkout securely.\n\n---\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### 1. Set the Base URL\nAll requests use the `{{url}}` variable as the base URL. Before making any requests, set this variable in your active environment:\n\n- Open the **DEV** environment (or create a new one)\n- Add a variable named `url` and set its value to the base URL of the Snow Rush API (e.g., `https://your-api-host.com`)\n\n### 2. Authenticate\nYou must authenticate before accessing protected endpoints:\n\n1. Use the **Register** request in the **Authentication** folder to create a new account, or use **Login** if you already have one.\n2. After a successful login, copy the token from the response.\n3. Store the token in your environment (e.g., as `{{token}}`) and ensure your requests include it in the `Authorization` header.\n\n> **Admin access:** Use the **Login (Admin)** request to authenticate as an admin and unlock product management endpoints.\n\n### 3. Start Making Requests\nOnce authenticated, you can explore the full API:\n- Browse and filter products via the **Products** and **Filtering** folders\n- Add items to your cart using the **Basket** folder\n- Place and track orders through the **Orders** folder\n\n---\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "29665995"
  },
